# ===================================================
# SmartPerfetto Configuration
# ===================================================
# Do not edit .env.example directly. Copy this file to the env file used by
# your run mode:
#   Local source: cp backend/.env.example backend/.env
#   Docker:       cp .env.example .env
#
# For local source runs, if `claude` already works in this terminal, keep all
# AI credential lines commented. The Claude Agent SDK can reuse Claude Code's
# local auth/config, including Claude Code-configured third-party providers.
# Docker cannot see your host Claude Code login, so Docker runs need either the
# UI Provider Manager or one explicit provider block below.
#
# Short answer: Claude Code, OpenAI Agents SDK, Pi Agent Core, and OpenCode are
# alternatives. You do not configure multiple runtimes for first setup. Pick
# local `claude`, one Claude-compatible block, one OpenAI-compatible block, the
# Pi Agent Core block, the OpenCode block, or the UI Provider Manager.
#
# Beginner rule:
#   1. Uncomment exactly ONE provider block below. If a provider shows both
#      Claude-compatible and OpenAI-compatible alternatives, choose one side.
#   2. Replace only placeholders like your_*_api_key_here, sk-your-*, model IDs,
#      or Base URLs when your provider console says they differ.
#   3. Restart the backend/container after editing this file.
#   4. If a UI Provider Manager profile is active, it overrides this env file.
#      Choose System Default in the provider switcher to use this file again.

# ---------------------------------------------------
# Feature Flags
# ---------------------------------------------------
# Enterprise multi-tenant paths are under development and default off.
# SMARTPERFETTO_ENTERPRISE=false

# Optional private Android knowledge roots (absolute paths, separated by the
# platform path delimiter). The default is empty/deny. Registration, license
# acknowledgement, and provider-send consent are still required separately.
# SMARTPERFETTO_KNOWLEDGE_ROOTS=/absolute/path/to/android-internals-wiki

# ---------------------------------------------------
# AI Service Configuration
# ---------------------------------------------------
# SmartPerfetto supports these runtime paths:
#   - claude-agent-sdk (default): Claude Code / Anthropic-compatible providers.
#   - openai-agents-sdk: OpenAI Responses or OpenAI-compatible Chat Completions.
#   - pi-agent-core: optional public runtime for custom Pi Agent Core model
#     configuration and the shared SmartPerfetto analysis pipeline.
#   - opencode: optional public runtime for custom OpenCode/OpenAI-compatible
#     model configuration and the shared SmartPerfetto analysis pipeline.
# These are alternative runtime paths, not two setup steps to complete.
# For first setup, do not enable both ANTHROPIC_* and OPENAI_*. In advanced
# deployments where both are present, SMARTPERFETTO_AGENT_RUNTIME selects the
# active side. Without it, SmartPerfetto defaults to claude-agent-sdk.
# The UI Provider Manager can store both Claude-compatible and OpenAI-compatible
# Base URLs for one provider, then switch the SDK runtime without editing .env.
#
# You can use:
#
#   1. Local Claude Code setup — no env needed when `claude` already works
#   2. Direct Anthropic API — uncomment ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#   3. Direct OpenAI API — uncomment OPENAI_* block
#   4. Pi Agent Core — uncomment the Pi block below
#   5. OpenCode — uncomment the OpenCode block below
#   6. Claude Code-compatible provider — uncomment ONE provider block below
#   7. Custom proxy/gateway — use Anthropic-compatible or OpenAI-compatible env
#
# ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │  SmartPerfetto                                   │
# │       │ (Claude SDK, OpenAI SDK, Pi, or OpenCode)│
# │       ▼                                          │
# │  Local Claude Code auth/config OR explicit env   │
# │       │                                          │
# │       ├── Anthropic / Claude-compatible          │
# │       ├── OpenAI / OpenAI-compatible             │
# │       │      OpenAI / Ollama / gateway / ...     │
# │       ├── Pi Agent Core custom model config      │
# │       └── OpenCode custom model config           │
# └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

# ===================================================
# Option 1: Local Claude Code (default for source runs)
# ===================================================
# No variables required here. Verify with:
#   claude

# ===================================================
# Option 2: Anthropic Direct
# ===================================================
# Get your API key at https://console.anthropic.com/
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here
# CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# CLAUDE_LIGHT_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5

# ===================================================
# Option 3: OpenAI Direct
# ===================================================
# Uses the OpenAI Agents SDK. No Anthropic compatibility proxy is required.
# Keep official OpenAI on the Responses API. Use chat_completions only for
# OpenAI-compatible gateways that do not implement Responses.
# SMARTPERFETTO_AGENT_RUNTIME=openai-agents-sdk
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# OPENAI_AGENTS_PROTOCOL=responses
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5.5
# OPENAI_LIGHT_MODEL=gpt-5.4-mini

# ===================================================
# Option 3b: Pi Agent Core
# ===================================================
# Pi Agent Core is optional. With a real model config it uses SmartPerfetto's
# shared prompt, SQL/Skill, plan/hypothesis, and report pipeline.
# SmartPerfetto loads @earendil-works/pi-agent-core only when this runtime is
# selected. It does not enable .pi project discovery, package extensions, shell
# tools, or file tools.
# Prefer Provider Manager custom providers for this runtime. For env fallback:
# SMARTPERFETTO_AGENT_RUNTIME=pi-agent-core
# SMARTPERFETTO_PI_AGENT_CORE_MODEL_JSON={"id":"your-model-id","name":"Your Model","api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","baseUrl":"https://api.openai.com/v1","reasoning":false,"input":["text"],"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0},"contextWindow":128000,"maxTokens":4096,"apiKeyEnv":"OPENAI_API_KEY"}
# Use "api":"openai-completions" for OpenAI-compatible chat/completions
# gateways; the example above targets official OpenAI Responses.
# Optional: use a local package checkout or unpacked npm package.
# SMARTPERFETTO_PI_AGENT_CORE_MODULE_PATH=/absolute/path/to/@earendil-works/pi-agent-core/dist/index.js
# Optional runtime-level prompt; SmartPerfetto analysis contracts still come
# from backend strategies.
# SMARTPERFETTO_PI_AGENT_CORE_SYSTEM_PROMPT=

# ===================================================
# Option 3c: OpenCode
# ===================================================
# OpenCode is optional. It runs a hardened isolated OpenCode server, uses
# explicit Provider Manager/env model configuration, and exposes only
# request-scoped SmartPerfetto MCP tools. It does not read your personal
# OpenCode login, project config, extensions, shell tools, or file tools.
# Prefer Provider Manager custom providers for this runtime. For env fallback:
# SMARTPERFETTO_AGENT_RUNTIME=opencode
# Recommended when you want OpenCode-specific model/provider wiring:
# SMARTPERFETTO_OPENCODE_MODEL_JSON={"providerID":"smartperfetto","modelID":"your-model-id","baseUrl":"https://api.openai.com/v1","apiKeyEnv":"OPENAI_API_KEY","smallModel":"your-light-model"}
# Or omit SMARTPERFETTO_OPENCODE_MODEL_JSON and use OPENAI_BASE_URL,
# OPENAI_API_KEY, OPENAI_MODEL, and OPENAI_LIGHT_MODEL below.
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_provider_api_key_here
# OPENAI_MODEL=your-model-id
# OPENAI_LIGHT_MODEL=your-light-model
# Optional: use a local package checkout or unpacked npm package.
# SMARTPERFETTO_OPENCODE_SDK_MODULE_PATH=/absolute/path/to/@opencode-ai/sdk/dist/index.js
# Optional: isolated project directory; otherwise SmartPerfetto creates a temp directory.
# SMARTPERFETTO_OPENCODE_PROJECT_DIR=/absolute/path/to/empty/project
# Optional runtime-level prompt; SmartPerfetto analysis contracts still come
# from backend strategies.
# SMARTPERFETTO_OPENCODE_SYSTEM_PROMPT=

# ===================================================
# Option 4: AWS Bedrock (Bearer Token)
# ===================================================
# Use Claude via AWS Bedrock with bearer token authentication.
# Bedrock requires cross-region inference model IDs (us.anthropic.*-v1:0);
# Anthropic-style short names like 'claude-sonnet-4-6' are rejected with
# HTTP 400 invalid model identifier. See GitHub issue #179.
# CLAUDE_CODE_USE_BEDROCK=1
# ANTHROPIC_BEDROCK_BASE_URL=https://bedrock-runtime.us-east-1.amazonaws.com
# AWS_BEARER_TOKEN_BEDROCK=your_bearer_token_here
# CLAUDE_MODEL=us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929-v1:0
# CLAUDE_LIGHT_MODEL=us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0

# ===================================================
# Option 5: Third-party provider presets
# ===================================================
# Uncomment ONE runtime side for ONE provider. Treat prefilled Base URLs as
# starting points; usually you only replace the key, but provider-console URLs
# take precedence.
# SmartPerfetto uses CLAUDE_MODEL and CLAUDE_LIGHT_MODEL. Claude Code docs may
# call these ANTHROPIC_MODEL / ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_HAIKU_MODEL; do not rename them
# in SmartPerfetto env files.
# Prefilled Base URLs below are based on public provider information and may be
# incomplete, stale, account-specific, or region-specific. If analysis fails at
# connection/tool-call time, verify both the Base URL and model IDs in your
# provider console first. Please open an issue or PR when a public preset needs
# to be corrected.
#
# Auth variable:
#   - ANTHROPIC_API_KEY sends X-Api-Key.
#   - ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN sends Authorization: Bearer <token>.
# Use the variable shown in each provider's official Claude Code guide.

# ---------------------------------------------------
# GLM / Z.ai (智谱AI / ZhipuAI)
# ---------------------------------------------------
# Console: https://open.bigmodel.cn/
# Claude/Anthropic-compatible Base URL:
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://open.bigmodel.cn/api/anthropic
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_zhipuai_api_key_here
# CLAUDE_MODEL=glm-5.1
# CLAUDE_LIGHT_MODEL=glm-4.5-air
#
# OpenAI-compatible Base URL:
# SMARTPERFETTO_AGENT_RUNTIME=openai-agents-sdk
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://open.bigmodel.cn/api/paas/v4
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_zhipuai_api_key_here
# OPENAI_AGENTS_PROTOCOL=chat_completions
# OPENAI_MODEL=glm-5.1
# OPENAI_LIGHT_MODEL=glm-4.5-air

